appnIsInP2SFmdBytes.name: appnIsInP2SFmdBytes
appnIsInP2SFmdBytes.description: Number of FMD bytes sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU since the counts were last activated.

appnIsInS2PFmdBytes.name: appnIsInS2PFmdBytes
appnIsInS2PFmdBytes.description: Number of FMD bytes sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU since the counts were last activated.

appnIsInP2SNonFmdBytes.name: appnIsInP2SNonFmdBytes
appnIsInP2SNonFmdBytes.description: Number of non-FMD bytes sent from the Primary LU to the Secondary LU since the counts were last activated.

appnIsInS2PNonFmdBytes.name: appnIsInS2PNonFmdBytes
appnIsInS2PNonFmdBytes.description: Number of non-FMD bytes sent from the Secondary LU to the Primary LU since the counts were last activated.

appnIsInPsAdjCpName.name: appnIsInPsAdjCpName
appnIsInPsAdjCpName.description: The primary stage adjacent CP name of this session. If the session stage traverses an RTP connection, the CP name of the remote RTP endpoint is returned.

appnIsInPsAdjTgNum.name: appnIsInPsAdjTgNum
appnIsInPsAdjTgNum.description: The primary stage adjacent transmission group (TG) number associated with this session. If the session stage traverses an RTP connection, the value 256 is returned. Values between 257 and 300 are available for other possible TG 'stand-ins' that may be added to APPN in the future.

appnIsInPsSendMaxBtuSize.name: appnIsInPsSendMaxBtuSize
appnIsInPsSendMaxBtuSize.description: The primary stage maximum basic transmission unit (BTU) size for sending data.

appnIsInPsSendPacingType.name: appnIsInPsSendPacingType
appnIsInPsSendPacingType.description: The primary stage type of pacing being used for sending data.

appnIsInPsSendRpc.name: appnIsInPsSendRpc
appnIsInPsSendRpc.description: The primary stage send residual pace count. This represents the primary stage number of message units (MUs) that can still be sent in the current session window.

appnIsInPsSendNxWndwSize.name: appnIsInPsSendNxWndwSize
appnIsInPsSendNxWndwSize.description: The primary stage size of the next window which will be used to send data.

appnIsInPsRecvPacingType.name: appnIsInPsRecvPacingType
appnIsInPsRecvPacingType.description: The primary stage type of pacing being used for receiving data.

appnIsInPsRecvRpc.name: appnIsInPsRecvRpc
appnIsInPsRecvRpc.description: The primary stage receive residual pace count. This represents the primary stage number of message units (MUs) that can still be received in the current session window.

appnIsInPsRecvNxWndwSize.name: appnIsInPsRecvNxWndwSize
appnIsInPsRecvNxWndwSize.description: The primary stage size of the next window which will be used to receive data.

appnIsInSsAdjCpName.name: appnIsInSsAdjCpName
appnIsInSsAdjCpName.description: The secondary stage adjacent CP name of this session. If the session stage traverses an RTP connection, the CP name of the remote RTP endpoint is returned.

appnIsInSsAdjTgNum.name: appnIsInSsAdjTgNum
appnIsInSsAdjTgNum.description: The secondary stage adjacent transmission group (TG) number associated with this session. If the session stage traverses an RTP connection, the value 256 is returned. Values between 257 and 300 are available for other possible TG 'stand-ins' that may be added to APPN in the future.

appnIsInSsSendMaxBtuSize.name: appnIsInSsSendMaxBtuSize
appnIsInSsSendMaxBtuSize.description: The secondary stage maximum basic transmission unit (BTU) size for sending data.

appnIsInSsSendPacingType.name: appnIsInSsSendPacingType
appnIsInSsSendPacingType.description: The secondary stage type of pacing being used for sending data.

appnIsInSsSendRpc.name: appnIsInSsSendRpc
appnIsInSsSendRpc.description: The secondary stage send residual pace count. This represents the secondary stage number of message units (MUs) that can still be sent in the current session window.

appnIsInSsSendNxWndwSize.name: appnIsInSsSendNxWndwSize
appnIsInSsSendNxWndwSize.description: The secondary stage size of the next window which will be used to send data.

appnIsInSsRecvPacingType.name: appnIsInSsRecvPacingType
appnIsInSsRecvPacingType.description: The secondary stage type of pacing being used for receiving data.

appnIsInSsRecvRpc.name: appnIsInSsRecvRpc
appnIsInSsRecvRpc.description: The secondary stage receive residual pace count. This represents the secondary stage number of message units (MUs) that can still be received in the current session window.

appnIsInSsRecvNxWndwSize.name: appnIsInSsRecvNxWndwSize
appnIsInSsRecvNxWndwSize.description: The secondary stage size of the next window which will be used to receive data.

appnIsInRouteInfo.name: appnIsInRouteInfo
appnIsInRouteInfo.description: The route selection control vector (RSCV X'2B') used for this session. It is present for APPN nodes; but is not present for LEN nodes. The format of this vector is described in SNA Formats. If no RSCV is available, a zero-length string is returned.

appnIsInRtpNceId.name: appnIsInRtpNceId
appnIsInRtpNceId.description: The HPR local Network Connection Endpoint of the session.

appnIsInRtpTcid.name: appnIsInRtpTcid
appnIsInRtpTcid.description: The RTP connection local TCID of the session.

appnIsRtpTable.name: appnIsRtpTable
appnIsRtpTable.description: A table indicating how many ISR sessions are transported by each RTP connection.

appnIsRtpEntry.name: appnIsRtpEntry
appnIsRtpEntry.description: Entry of Intermediate Session RTP Table.

appnIsRtpNceId.name: appnIsRtpNceId
appnIsRtpNceId.description: The local Network Connection Endpoint of the RTP connection.

appnIsRtpTcid.name: appnIsRtpTcid
